(84, 'multiplechoice', 26283618, 'Generic Parent', 'Miscellaneous', 'No', NULL, NULL, 5, 'A patient with adhesive capsulitis took time off work but now his employers are telling him to return to work. You examine the patient and his range of movements are better now. But the patient is saying he can’t go back to work as it will aggravate pain. What will be your next appropriate step as his GP?', 'A', 'Arrange vocational counseling of patient', 'Arrange functional assessment', 'Tell patient he has to go back to work', 'Speak to his employers and tell them they cannot return', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(85, 'multiplechoice', 26283645, 'Generic Parent', 'Respiratory', 'No', NULL, NULL, 5, 'A lady with 18 weeks\' gestation and previous DVT, present with sudden dyspnea and shortness of breath. She had a history of DVT. What\'s the choice of investigation in this pt?', 'B', 'D-dimer', 'V/Q scan', 'ECG', 'CTPA', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(86, 'multiplechoice', 26283679, 'Generic Parent', 'Gynae & Obs', 'No', NULL, NULL, 5, 'A 27-year-old female presents to her OB/GYN for a check-up. During her visit, a pelvic exam and Pap smear are performed. The patient does not have any past medical issues and has had routine gynecologic care with normal pap smears every 3 years since age 21. The results of the Pap smear demonstrate atypical squamous cells of undetermined significance (ASCUS). Which of the following is the next best step in the management of this patient?', 'B', 'Repeat Pap smear in 1 year', 'Perform an HPV DNA test', 'Repeat Pap smear in 3 years', 'Perform colposcopy', 'Perform a Loop Electrosurgical Excision Procedure (LEEP)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(87, 'multiplechoice', 26283717, 'Generic Parent', 'Gynae & Obs', 'No', NULL, NULL, 5, 'A pregnant woman with vaginal bleeding has blood group 0-ve. How will you assess anti-D dose?', 'A', 'Feto-maternal haemorrhage', 'Assesmentof anti-D Ig', 'Coombs test', 'USG', 'kell test', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(88, 'multiplechoice', 26283745, 'Generic Parent', 'Ethics', 'No', NULL, NULL, 5, 'One old lady was under clinical trial of a drug of a company for Alzheimer\'s. Her MMSE was 24 at the time of initiation which decreased upto 15 now. Son wants to continue with trial. Who will decide?', 'B', 'Yourself', 'Ethics committee', 'Her family member', 'Pharma company', 'Senior doctors', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(89, 'multiplechoice', 26283775, 'Generic Parent', 'Gynae & Obs', 'No', NULL, NULL, 5, 'Hypoechoic mass in right breast in 23 year old female. What is the most likely diagnosis?', 'C', 'Cancer', 'Ductoma', 'Fibroadenoma', 'Mastitis', 'Necrosis', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(90, 'multiplechoice', 26283883, 'Generic Parent', 'Gynae & Obs', 'No', NULL, NULL, 5, 'A 25-year-old G1P0 presents to her obstetrician’s office for a routine prenatal visit at 32 weeks\' gestation. At this visit, she feels well and has no complaints. Her pregnancy has been uncomplicated, aside from her Rh negative status, for which she received Rhogam at 28 weeks\' gestation. The patient has a past medical history of mild intermittent asthma and migraine headaches. She currently uses her albuterol inhaler once a week and takes prenatal vitamins. Her temperature is 98.6°F (37.0°C), pulse is 70/min, blood pressure is 120/70 mmHg, and respirations are 13/min. Cardiopulmonary exam is unremarkable, and abdominal exam reveals a gravid uterus with fundal height at 30 centimeters. Bedside ultrasound reveals that the fetus is in transverse lie. The patient states that she prefers to have a vaginal delivery. Which of the following is the best next step in management?', 'A', 'Expectant management', 'Weekly ultrasound', 'External cephalic version', 'Internal cephalic version', 'Caesarean section at 38 weeks', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(91, 'multiplechoice', 26283911, 'Generic Parent', 'Paediatrics', 'No', NULL, NULL, 5, '18 months old child with harsh cough and inspiratory stridor. Fever is 38*C. How will u manage?', 'B', 'Nebs with salbutamol', 'Oral prednisolone', 'Antibiotic', 'Iv dexamethasone', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(92, 'multiplechoice', 26283935, 'Generic Parent', 'Ethics', 'No', NULL, NULL, 5, 'A patient is waiting next to talkative schizophrenia patient. He complains about that to you. What should you do?', 'C', 'Make the schizophrenic patient wait in severe psychiatric patients waiting room', 'Arrange the different schedule for each of them', 'Confronts patient\'s concern', 'Tell him that the patient is schizophrenic', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(93, 'multiplechoice', 26283961, 'Generic Parent', 'Miscellaneous', 'No', NULL, NULL, 5, 'A concerned mother presents to clinic stating that her 14-year-old son has not gone through his growth spurt. She states that, although shorter, he had been growing at the same rate as his peers until the past year. There is no evidence of delayed puberty in the mother, but the father\'s history is unknown. The patient has no complaints. On physical exam, the patient is a healthy-appearing 14-year-old boy whose height is below the third percentile and whose weight is at the 50th percentile. His bone age is determined to be 11 years. A laboratory workup, including thyroid stimulating hormone (TSH), is unremarkable. What is the most likely diagnosis?', 'A', 'Constitutional growth delay', 'Familial short stature', 'Hypothyroidism', 'Growth hormone deficiency', 'Celiac disease', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(94, 'multiplechoice', 26283992, 'Generic Parent', 'Surgery', 'No', NULL, NULL, 5, 'A middle age man came with the complaint of painful defecation with blood in the stool. Pain relieved after half an hour. Otherwise , he has no problem. On examination, digital rectal examination can’t be performed as he has anal pain. What next appropriate treatment?', 'A', 'GTN ointment', 'Lateral sphincterotomy', 'Saline bath and high fiber diet', 'Corticosteroid cream', 'NSAID gel to relief pain', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(95, 'multiplechoice', 26284040, 'Generic Parent', 'Surgery', 'No', NULL, NULL, 5, 'Young man with mucopurulent discharge in perineum. Otherwise past med h/o normal. No other problem. Pic shown was a hairy natal cleft and there was an 1cm red lesion with opening. What is the diagnosis?[cmimg]0/9406627_F4OZ6EPT.jpg[/cmimg]', 'A', 'Pilonidal sinus', 'Chronic anal gland sepsis', 'Thrombosed external hemorrhoid', 'Crohn’s disease', 'Ulcerative colitis', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(96, 'multiplechoice', 26284049, 'Generic Parent', 'Psychiatry', 'No', NULL, NULL, 5, 'When asking a patient about family history of psychiatric illness she said: ‘Oh now you ask about that, you know whales, whales are good, them oil are useful. Lit up the whole city. Grandpa worked on the whaler , and then , of course we are all very sane’. What is this condition called?', 'A', 'Derailment', 'Tangentiality', 'Circumstantiality', 'Flight of ideas', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(97, 'multiplechoice', 26284068, 'Generic Parent', 'Miscellaneous', 'No', NULL, NULL, 5, 'A man who was smoker and drinks alcohol was having complaint weakness on walking. On further inquiry there was history of intermittent claudication from back thigh to legs bilateral. He has problem in walking both downhill and uphill. One is 200 meter another is 20 meter . Right ABI 0.8, left ABI 0.9, On examination after exercise weak dorsiflexion. All pulse are palpable. What will you do next?', 'B', 'Doppler venous for DVT', 'arterial Doppler lower limbs', 'angiography', 'ct of spine', 'MRI lumbosacral spine', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(98, 'multiplechoice', 26284206, 'Generic Parent', 'Surgery', 'No', NULL, NULL, 5, 'A 15-year-old boy presents to the emergency room with severe lower abdominal pain that awoke him from sleep about 3 hours ago. The pain is sharp and radiates to his left thigh. While in the emergency room, the patient experiences one episode of vomiting. His temperature is 99.3°F (37.4°C), blood pressure is 130/80 mmHg, pulse is 119/min, respirations are 14/min, and oxygen saturation is 99% on room air. Abdominal examination reveals no tenderness in all 4 quadrants. Scrotal examination reveals an elevated left testicle that is diffusely tender. Stroking of the patient\'s inner thigh on the left side does not result in elevation of the testicle. What is the next step in the management of this patient?', 'D', 'CT scan of abdomen and pelvis', 'IV antibiotics', 'Observation and morphine', 'Surgical exploration', 'Testicular doppler ultrasound', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
