(213, 'multiplechoice', 26841678, 'Generic Parent', 'Paediatrics', 'No', 'lncreased gastric residues in a preterm neonate is highly suspicious for Necrotizing enterocolitis. The condition usually presents at 3-1 0 days after birth, and is due to bowel wall injury resulting from perinatal asphyxia. The diagnosis requires a high index of suspicion. Treatment depends on the degree of bowel involvement and severity of presentation. Pre term neonates are at high risk for other complications such as hyaline membrane disease, which presents with respiratory distress and ground glass appearance of the lungs on chest x-rays. Also Grunting is always a bad sign for any new born and there will be failure to thrive.(Choice A} Tracheo-esophageal fistula presents with excessive drooling, choking, coughing, and cyanosisdue to aspiration of feedings.(Choice C) Bilious vomiting without abdominal distention is the cardinal sign for duodenal atresia.(Choice D) Clinical features of meconium aspiration syndrome include thick, greenish amniotic fluid in the mouth and throat at birth, accompanied by cyanosis and respiratory distress.(Choice E) Pyloric stenosis is characterized by projectile nonbilious vomiting and palpation of an olive-shaped mass immediately after the infant has vomited.', 'lncreased gastric residues in a preterm neonate is highly suspicious for Necrotizing enterocolitis. The condition usually presents at 3-1 0 days after birth, and is due to bowel wall injury resulting from perinatal asphyxia. The diagnosis requires a high index of suspicion. Treatment depends on the degree of bowel involvement and severity of presentation. Pre term neonates are at high risk for other complications such as hyaline membrane disease, which presents with respiratory distress and ground glass appearance of the lungs on chest x-rays. Also Grunting is always a bad sign for any new born and there will be failure to thrive.(Choice A} Tracheo-esophageal fistula presents with excessive drooling, c