(510, 'multiplechoice', 30741822, 'Generic Parent', 'Ophthalmology', 'No', NULL, NULL, 5, 'A 45-year-old man comes to the emergency department with complaint of severe pain in his left eye. The pain started 3 hours ago, and is associated with blurred vision and nausea. On examination, the patient has stable vitals. The left eye is reddened and hard to palpation. The I visual acuity of the left and right eyes are 6/18 and 6/12 respectively. There is no history of trauma to the eye. Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?', 'D', 'Acute retinal artery occlusion', 'Acute retinal vein thrombosis', 'Open-angle glaucoma', 'Acute closed-angle glaucoma', 'Cataract', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
