(671, 'multiplechoice', 31639774, 'Generic Parent', 'Paediatrics Mock-1', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 5, 'A 4-year-oid child is brought in by his daycare provider because the child is extremely irritable and refuses to eat. The child refuses to lean back, speaks in muffled wards, looks extremely ill, and is drooling. CXR shows a positive thumb- print sign. What is the most appropriate next step in management?', 'A', ' Intubate', 'Racemic epinephrine ', 'Empiric antibiotics ', 'Physical examination ', 'CT neck ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
