(673, 'multiplechoice', 31639787, 'Generic Parent', 'Paediatrics Mock-1', 'Yes', NULL, NULL, 5, 'A 7-year-old girl is brought to the clinic by her mother due to a persistent postnasal drip and repeated episodes of a runny nose. in the winter, she experiences several episodes of upper respiratory tract infections, which last for two to three weeks at a time. She snores, and is unable to smell her favorite food. Her immunizations are up-to-date. On examination, she is mildly underweight for her age. She has a runny nose, and her nasal drainage is colorless and stringy. Nasal inspection reveals bilateral nasal polyps, and auscultation of the chest reveals coarse rales. What is the one condition that you would like to rule out in this child? ', 'B', 'Leukemia', 'Cystic fibrosis', 'Foreign body aspiration', 'Nasal septal deviation', 'Allergic rhinitis', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
